@startuml summarize-overview
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #555555

title dev-workgraph — **summarize** (§3)\nPer-commit **model layer** via **commitModel** (Ollama / LM Studio)

legend top left
  |= Tag |= Meaning |
  | **(D) input** | From **evidence** — not modified |
  | **(M:c) model** | Interpretation — may be wrong |
  | **(D) post** | CLI post-processing after LLM |
  | **(H) init** | project.json grounding |
endlegend

rectangle "**Precondition**" #FFF8E1 {
  card "**evidence** done\ncommits/<ts>/<hash>.json\n+ .patch or .partN.*" as EVID
  card "**init** (recommended)\nproject.json" as INIT
}

rectangle "**summarize (M:c)**" #FFF3E0 {
  card "Read evidence +\nwrite **summaries/**" as IN
  card "LLM commitModel\n(Ollama | LM Studio)\n1× normal · N× split + finalize" as LLM
  card "**canonical** summaries/<ts>/<hash>.json" as OUT
}

EVID --> IN
INIT ..> LLM : project context block\n-> system prompt
IN --> LLM
LLM --> OUT

note bottom of OUT
  **Per commit the model layer adds:**
  • **signals** evaluated (technical / architecture / security)
  • **questionsAnalysis[]** (role-aware, 4 after finalize)
  • summary, changeTypes, technologies, confidence
  ----
  **Skip** if canonical summary exists.
  **Empty patch:** provenance.model = **(none)**, no LLM.
  **Split:** .partN.json → .merge.json → finalize → canonical.
  **--limit N** for trials. **--period** scopes data dir.
end note

@enduml


@startuml summarize-command
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF3E0

title **summarize** — Full command flow

start

:Resolve repo → repo-id;\ncommits dir = commits/ or periods/<id>/commits/;

:List evidence commits/**/*.json;

if (None found?) then (yes)
  #Pink:Run **evidence** first;
  stop
else (no)
endif

:Pick **commitModel**\n(Ollama / LM Studio);\n--model overrides;\nsaved in config.llm.commit;

:loadProjectContext(repo [, period]);
note right
  Prefer periods/<id>/project.json,
  fallback to repo-level project.json
end note

if (project.json missing?) then (yes)
  #FFF9C4:⚠️ Warn;\nempty project context block;
else (no)
  :Build projectContextBlock → prepend to system;
endif

:system = projectContextBlock + COMMIT_SUMMARY_SYSTEM;

:Build **pending** list;
note right
  Skip if **summaries/<ts>/<hash>.json** exists
  (canonical only — not .merge.json)
  Optional --limit N on pending slice
end note

if (pending empty?) then (yes)
  stop
else (no)
endif

partition "Per commit" {
  if (record.split?) then (yes)
    #LightBlue:→ **split path** (see summarize-split-commit);
  else (no)
    :Read commits/<ts>/.json + .patch;
  endif

  if (**isEmptySummarizePatch**(patch)?) then (yes)
    :Write empty ModelLayer;\nprovenance.model = **(none)**;
    note right: skipped (empty patch)\nno LLM call
  else (has diff hunks)
    repeat
      :chatJson — Ollama or LM Studio\nformat / response_format = modelJsonSchema();
      :extract + schema-validate;
    repeat while (fail?) is (yes)
    ->no;
    note right: Up to **3 attempts** with backoff

    if (All attempts failed?) then (yes)
      :Log failed;\n**no canonical summary**;
    else (success)
      :**enforceSignalReasons** (D post);
      :Attach **provenance** (D post);
      :Write **summaries/<ts>/<hash>.json**;\ncommits/ unchanged;
    endif
  endif
}

#LightGreen:✅ Summarized N, failed M, skipped empty K;

stop

@enduml


@startuml summarize-model-layer
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classBackgroundColor #FAFAFA

title **ModelLayer** — canonical schema (§3)\n`summaries/<ts>/<hash>.json` · interpretation, not evidence

class "CommitSummaryRecord\n(after summarize)" as CR {
  commitHash, timestamp, title, author
  deterministic : DeterministicLayer **(D, from evidence)**
  model : ModelLayer **(M:c)**
}

class "ModelLayer\n**(M:c) — from LLM backend**" as MOD #FFF3E0 {
  ..
  **Narrative**
  --
  **summary** : string
  Plain-language WHAT the diff changed.
  NOT importance, impact, or production use.
  PATCH is source of truth, not commit message.
  ROUTINE_RULE: deps/CI/format → name plainly,
  no version numbers; substantive only if mixed.
  --
  **changeTypes[]** : enum tags
  feature | bugfix | refactoring | security
  | infrastructure | testing | configuration
  | developer-tooling | architecture
  | documentation | deployment
  (zero or more)
  --
  **technologies[]** : string[]
  Languages, frameworks, tools, protocols
  **visible in the patch only** — no guessing.
  --
  ..
  **Signals** (low | medium | high only)
  --
  **technicalSignal**
  Technical depth / complexity of the change
  --
  **architectureSignal**
  Effect on structure, boundaries, modules,
  system design
  --
  **securitySignal**
  Authn, authz, identity, data protection,
  permissions, platform security
  --
  **signalReasons** { technical, architecture, security }
  One-line justification **grounded in patch**.
  Required when signal ≠ low.
  --
  ..
  **Missing context (primary output)**
  --
  **questionsAnalysis[]** : string[]
  What a human must answer — Git cannot know.
  Framed by **role** (via project context).
  Split finalize: exactly **4** items.
  Unknowns go here, never inferred in summary.
  --
  **confidence** : low | medium | high
  Model's confidence in its own summary
}

class "provenance\n**(D) — CLI attaches**" as PROV #E3F2FD {
  model : model name or **(none)**
  generatedAt : ISO timestamp
}

MOD *-- PROV

note right of MOD
  **Not produced by the model** — added after generation.
  Empty patch: **(none)** provenance, blank summary.
  On validation failure after 3 retries: no canonical file.
end note

CR *-- MOD

@enduml


@startuml summarize-prompts
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title **summarize** — Prompt assembly\n(system + user -> model JSON)

package "**System prompt**" #FFFDE7 {
  component "projectContextBlock\n(from init, optional)" as CTX
  component "COMMIT_SUMMARY_SYSTEM" as SYS
}

package "**User prompt**\nbuildCommitUserPrompt (D inputs)" #E8F5E9 {
  component "Metadata" as META
  component "Patch body" as PATCH
}

package "**LLM output**" as OUT #FFF3E0 {
  component "commitModel" as LLM
  [ModelLayer JSON\nschema-validated]
}

note right of CTX
  **roleDefinitionPromptBlock** (from role-definitions.ts):
  matrix level, impact sphere,
  question + CV emphasis, doNotClaim
  profile.summary, domains, stack, themes
  story.preparedContext
  Frame questions for role
  Role in **system** only — not in user patch
  NEVER inflate impact because of context
end note

note right of SYS
  Patch = SOURCE OF TRUTH (not commit message)
  summary / technologies / signals / questions rules
  No team / they / we — one developer's commit
  No production / ownership / business impact claims
  ROUTINE_RULE (shared across pipeline)
end note

note right of META
  Commit message — CONTEXT ONLY, may be wrong
  Areas touched (from deterministic)
  Files added / modified / deleted / renamed
  Churn +lines / -lines
end note

note right of PATCH
  diff block (max 16000 chars)
  deterministic layer is read-only input —
  summarize never rewrites changedFiles, areas, churn
end note

CTX --> SYS : withProjectContext()
SYS --> LLM
META --> LLM
PATCH --> LLM

LLM --> OUT

@enduml


@startuml summarize-init-context
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title How **init** shapes the **model layer** (not deterministic)

rectangle "**role-definitions.ts**\n(questionEmphasisForRole)" as RD #FFF8E1

map "Per-repo role → question emphasis" as ROLES {
  Principal Developer => system-wide trade-offs, cross-team boundaries,\nlong-term architectural consequences, org-scale production adoption
  Staff Developer => design ownership across subsystems,\nplatform direction, integration with adjacent systems
  Senior Developer => feature/design ownership, customer or product driver,\nreplacing manual processes, mentoring or review scope
  Middle Developer => feature/module ownership, design input vs execution-only,\nproduction support scope, collaboration across teams
  Junior Developer => assigned vs self-directed work, learning context,\nscope of autonomy, who reviewed or unblocked
  Principal Frontend Developer => cross-product frontend architecture,\ndesign-system/platform standards, org-scale UX adoption
  Staff Frontend Developer => frontend subsystem ownership,\ndesign-system/platform direction, API contract integration
  Senior Frontend Developer => feature-level UI ownership, component architecture,\nUX/product driver context, mentoring or review scope
  Middle Frontend Developer => shipped UI features/flows, component ownership,\naccessibility responsibility, API integration scope
  Junior Frontend Developer => assigned vs self-directed UI work,\ndesign handoff vs implementation-only, who reviewed or unblocked
}

rectangle "init → project.json" as PJ #FFF8E1
rectangle "Influences via **system** prompt" as INF #FFFDE7 {
  card "**summary** — patch-grounded;\nproject context for interpretation only" as S
  card "**questionsAnalysis[]** — role-aware gaps\n(roleDefinitionPromptBlock + emphasis)" as Q
  card "**signals** — patch only;\nNOT role-calibrated" as SIG
  card "**NOT** used to inflate impact\n(doNotClaim guard)" as X
}

PJ --> INF
RD ..> ROLES
ROLES ..> Q

note bottom
  Without init: warn + summarize with empty context block.
  Full competency text at init (console only);
  LLM gets compact ROLE DEFINITION block.
  Role shapes **which gaps to ask about**, not signal levels.
end note

@enduml


@startuml summarize-signals
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF3E0

title **Signals** — generation, validation, downstream use

rectangle "Model produces (M:c)" as GEN {
  card "technicalSignal" as TS
  card "architectureSignal" as AS
  card "securitySignal" as SS
  card "signalReasons.{technical,\narchitecture, security}" as SR
}

rectangle "**enforceSignalReasons (D post)**" as ENF #E3F2FD {
  card "If signal ≠ low AND reason empty\n→ demote signal to **low**" as R
}

rectangle "Downstream (deterministic)" as DOWN #E8F5E9 {
  card "**tierOf(commit)**\nfor commit-group groups.tiers" as TIER
}

GEN --> ENF
ENF --> DOWN

note as N1
  **Scale:** low < medium < high only — **no numeric scores**
  Non-low **must** cite patch in signalReasons
  model: null → tier **low**
end note

note as N2
  **tierOf rules:**
  • **hi** — at least one signal is high
  • **medium** — at least one medium, none high
  • **low** — all low, OR model is null
  Used by commit-group to weight session history depth
end note

@enduml


@startuml summarize-questions
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FCE4EC

title **questionsAnalysis[]** — primary model output at commit level (§3, §8)

rectangle "**Purpose**" as P {
  card "Recover context Git **cannot** store:\nownership, intent, production use, customer driver"
}

rectangle "**Prompt rules (COMMIT_SUMMARY_SYSTEM)**" as RULES {
  card "Never claim unknowns in summary — put in questions"
  card "Message vs patch mismatch → question the gap"
  card "Role emphasis from projectContextBlock"
  card "Skip facts already in preparedContext / profile"
}

rectangle "**Typical probes**" as EX {
  card "Used in production or experimental?"
  card "Your own design or maintenance of someone else's?"
  card "Customer-driven or internal tooling?"
  card "Part of a security boundary?"
  card "Replacing a manual process?"
}

rectangle "**Downstream**" as DOWN #E3F2FD {
  card "commit-group — session questions\n(merge + reframe)"
  card "report — dedupe across folds"
  card "prepare — collapse to 4 questions"
  card "final — human answers → RECONSTRUCTION.md"
}

P --> RULES
RULES --> EX
EX --> DOWN

note bottom
  **Most important field** in the model layer at this stage.
  Summaries describe *what* changed; questions ask *what Git cannot know*.
end note

@enduml


@startuml summarize-sequence
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title Sequence — **summarize** per commit

actor "Developer" as DEV
database "commits/<ts>/\nevidence files" as COMM
database "summaries/<ts>/\ncanonical .json" as SUMM
database "project.json" as PJ
participant "**summarize**" as SUM
participant "LLM\ncommitModel\nOllama | LM Studio" as LLM

DEV -> SUM : dev-workgraph summarize ./repo\n[--period] [--limit N]

SUM -> COMM : list evidence manifests
SUM -> SUMM : skip if canonical exists
SUM -> PJ : loadProjectContext()
alt missing
  SUM --> DEV : ⚠️ no project context
end

loop each pending commit
  alt split commit
    SUM -> SUM : parts → merge → finalize (3× LLM)
  else normal
    SUM -> COMM : read .json + .patch
  end

  alt empty patch (no diff --git)
    SUM -> SUMM : write (none) provenance\nno LLM
  else substantive
    SUM -> LLM : chatJson(schema=modelJsonSchema)
    alt success
      LLM --> SUM : ModelLayer fields
      SUM -> SUM : enforceSignalReasons()\n+ provenance
      SUM -> SUMM : write canonical .json
    else failure
      SUM --> DEV : failed — no canonical file
    end
  end
end

SUM --> DEV : ✅ summarized N, failed M, skipped empty K

@enduml


@startuml summarize-example
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title Example — commit record **after summarize** (§3)

object "summaries/1717428123/b0648088.json" as REC #FFF3E0 {
  commitHash = "b0648088"
  title = "Production build and deployment automation"
  ..
  **deterministic (D — copied from evidence)**
  changedFiles.added = [assembly/production.xml, backend/build.sh, …]
  linesAdded = 214 · linesDeleted = 18
  areas = [backend, build-and-deploy]
  excludedFiles = [backend/package-lock.json]
  ..
  **model (M:c — from summarize)**
  summary = "Added Maven build profiles, ZIP assembly, …"
  changeTypes = [infrastructure, deployment, developer-tooling]
  technologies = [Maven, Node.js, …]
  technicalSignal = medium
  architectureSignal = medium
  securitySignal = low
  signalReasons.technical = "Introduces build tooling across Maven and Node…"
  signalReasons.architecture = "Defines deployment boundary and packaging…"
  signalReasons.security = "No auth/identity code touched."
  questionsAnalysis = [
    "Was this used for real production deployment, or experimental?",
    "Did this replace a manual deployment process?",
    "Was this your own work or a shared team effort?"
  ]
  confidence = medium
  provenance.model = "qwen2.5-coder:14b"
}

note bottom of REC
  deterministic = evidence (trustworthy)
  model = interpretation (may be wrong; cite patch in signals)
  questions = missing human context (primary product seed)
end note

@enduml


@startuml summarize-trust-boundary
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title **summarize** — what stays **(D)** vs what the **model** adds

legend left
  **Stays in commits/ (from evidence)**
  ----
  deterministic.* (files, churn, areas, excludedFiles)
  .patch or .partN.patch on disk
  commitHash, timestamp, title, author
  ----
  **Written to summaries/ (M:c)**
  ----
  summary, changeTypes[], technologies[]
  technical / architecture / security signals
  signalReasons (patch-grounded)
  questionsAnalysis[] (role-aware)
  confidence
  provenance (CLI; **(none)** if empty patch)
endlegend

note bottom
  Init context affects **prompt only** — never rewrites evidence files.
  Split audit: .partN.json, .merge.json (not used by commit-group).
  Production / ownership / impact: **never inferred** — only in questionsAnalysis.
end note

@enduml


@startuml summarize-split-commit
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #E3F2FD

title **summarize** — Split commit flow (6 steps)\nAutomatic inside **summarize** · no separate CLI

start

if (canonical summary exists?) then (yes)
  :Skip entire commit;
  stop
else (no)
endif

partition "[1/6] Summarize parts (M:c)" {
  while (more parts?) is (yes)
    if (part patch empty?) then (yes)
      :Write partN.json\nprovenance (none);
    else (no)
      :LLM to summaries/partN.json;
    endif
  endwhile (no)
}

partition "[2/6] Deterministic merge (D)" {
  :mergeCommitPartSummaries\nto hash.merge.json;
  note right
    Union signals, technologies,
    concat questionsAnalysis
  end note
}

if (merge exists and canonical missing?) then (resume)
  note right: Skip steps 1-2
else (fresh)
endif

partition "[3/6] Polish signalReasons (M:c)" {
  :LLM mergeFinalizeSignalReasons;
}
partition "[4/6] Compose summary (M:c)" {
  :LLM mergeFinalizeSummary;
}
partition "[5/6] Reframe questionsAnalysis (M:c)" {
  :LLM mergeFinalizeQuestions\nexactly 4 items;
}

partition "[6/6] Write canonical (D)" {
  :Write summaries/hash.json;
}

#LightGreen:✅ Split commit finalized;

stop

@enduml
